WE NEEDED A GUILD<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “What’s a guild?” I asked Merani.  <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “It’s a group of friends who adventure together,” she said.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “I thought a guild was the place I work with my trainer.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “That’s a different kind of guild.”<br>
<br>
I didn’t like their members in particular, but many of my fighting brethren in Qeynos were in a guild.  The idea sounded like a good one.  Folks of like mind, fighting together and questing together with a common cause.  How come THOSE people got invited to guilds?  Do you ask to join one?  Are guilds created at some massive city on the other side of the world?<br>
<br>
One evening while medding outside Blackburrow, a young lady was sitting nearby.  She was an Erudite wizard who wore a red cloak that wrapped cozily around her head.  When she sat to med, she always looked like she was bundled up from the cold.  She was alone… I was alone… and something about her looked very inviting.  I asked if she would group with me.  She accepted.  Her name was Cervania.<br>
<br>
It was exciting news to tell Montag the next night.  “I met this wizard!” I said.  “I think she’ll be a great addition to our team.”   And she was.  Always up for something new, Cervania grouped with Montag and me whenever she was around.  And I imagined… if I was in a guild, these are the kinds of friends I would want by my side.  <br>
<br>
            “How do I join a guild?” I asked Merani.<br>
            &quot;What guild do you want to join?” she replied.<br>
            “I don’t know.  But it sounds like fun.”<br>
            “It’s funny you ask, my friends and I were just talking about starting one.”<br>
            “Really?”<br>
<br>
I didn’t know what else to say.  It would be too presumptuous to even imply that I could join her.  Her friends were so far away, and so POWERFUL.  I had a long way to go before being in the league with Merani and her cronies.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “Would you be interested in joining our guild?” she asked.<br>
<br>
I about fell over… but tried not to show it.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp “I would be very honored.” <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=3.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.showNextMessage?topicID=3.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.eq-arrow-of-light.com/aol/images/boardbuttons/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.emailToFriend?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.threadControl?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthearrowoflightcommonsfrm23.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub66.ezboard.com/BBSFor